vehicles.name: CHTR T392 (Trailer, Short)
vehicles.description: The Class 392 'Transverse' is a Tram-Train manufactured by RRG Between 2018 and Today. They are designed to operate on Tram Networks, and switch to Heavy Rail Networks. They are able to run on 1.5 kV DC and 25 kV 60 Hz AC. They come in 5 Coach sets and have a Top speed of 120 km/h. But are Limited to 80 km/h when on Roads. They also have Low-Floor Boarding. They operate on SETN Tramlink and HRR Light Metro Lines.

vehicles.name: CHTR G553 (Trailer)
vehicles.description: The Class 553 'G441' is an Electric Multiple Unit manufactured by Rodani Rail between 2015 and 2023 for PNR's Nerkden and Elston Railway. They were Designed as 3 Coach Articulated sets due to the short Platforms. They come Equiped with Rack Railway equipment in order to Traverse the Steep grades in the Eastern parts of the Railway. They also have the ability to be Automatically Controlled via CBTC. The units have a Top speed of 120 km/h.

vehicles.name: CHTR C761 (Trailer)
